body:
Locally on my workspace these unit tests pass, but I added:

`static { Constants.SLOTS_PER_EPOCH = 4; }`

to the beginning of the `ValidatorApiHandlerTest` class and the exact 3 failures were reproduced. I then noticed that `PerformanceTrackerTest` has this [statement](https://github.com/PegaSysEng/teku/blob/master/validator/coordinator/src/test/java/tech/pegasys/teku/validator/coordinator/performance/PerformanceTrackerTest.java#L57-L60):

>   @BeforeAll
>   static void setUp() {
>     Constants.SLOTS_PER_EPOCH = 4;
>   }

But `Constants.SLOTS_PER_EPOCH` is never reset back to 8 ("minimal" configuration of the Constants class).

After looking at the failed builds on circleci, I saw that the `PerformanceTrackerTest` is run right before the `ValidatorApiHandlerTest`, so I'm thinking that `Constants.SLOTS_PER_EPOCH` is still left as 4 at the time `ValidatorApiHandlerTest` begins. When I run the `:validator:coordinator:test` task locally, `DepositProviderTest` is run in between `PerformanceTrackerTest` and `ValidatorApiHandlerTest` and resets the `Constants.SLOTS_PER_EPOCH` back to 8 which is likely why the tests pass locally. I believe resetting the Constants.SLOTS_PER_EPOCH back to 8 (the default value) in an @AfterAll function may fix it.

Note: I'm new here and have been going through the Teku code base in the past month with the help of @benjaminion as part of a challenge given to me to find a security vulnerability. I'm also new to circleci, so if there's a way to test this proposed change, I'd be happy to do that.
